OL,3,CScotland's first disability gold
OL,4,Ctournament tees off
OL,6,FThe Borders is hosting Scotland's
OL,7,Ffirst Open for golfers with
OL,8,Fdisabilities at Cardrona Golf Resort
OL,9,Fnear Peebles.
OL,11,FMore than 40 players from across the
OL,12,FUK, Ireland, and Australia are
OL,13,Fcompeting in the two-day tournament
OL,14,Fwhich aims to showcase inclusivity
OL,15,Fwithin the sport.
OL,17,FGolfers with a range of physical and
OL,18,Fmental impairments including amputees
OL,19,Fand paragolfers are taking part in the
OL,20,Fcompetition.
